<Link id="l00056" /><CodeLine lineNumber="56"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// ImmutableList - This class represents an immutable (functional) list.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00057" /><CodeLine lineNumber="57"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///  It is implemented as a smart pointer (wraps ImmutableListImpl), so it</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00058" /><CodeLine lineNumber="58"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///  it is intended to always be copied by value as if it were a pointer.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00059" /><CodeLine lineNumber="59"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///  This interface matches ImmutableSet and ImmutableMap.  ImmutableList</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00060" /><CodeLine lineNumber="60"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///  objects should almost never be created directly, and instead should</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00061" /><CodeLine lineNumber="61"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///  be created by ImmutableListFactory objects that manage the lifetime</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00062" /><CodeLine lineNumber="62"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///  of a group of lists.  When the factory object is reclaimed, all lists</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00063" /><CodeLine lineNumber="63"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///  created by that factory are released as well.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00064" /><CodeLine lineNumber="64"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">template</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &lt;</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">typename</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> T&gt;</span></CodeLine>
